         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Clearing the 700 MHz Band: Support Scheme for PMSE Equipment Owners</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>04/2018</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="75100000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Ofcom has a requirement for an Operator to administer the funding scheme for eligible PMSE owners and equipment.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="32340000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="32510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="63120000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72320000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="75110000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKI"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The radio spectrum between 470 MHz and 790 MHz is used by Digital Terrestrial Television (DTT) and Programme Making and Special Events (PMSE) services. In 11.2014, Ofcom published a statement setting out our decision to clear these services from the 700 MHz band (the part of the radio spectrum between 694 MHz and 790 MHz) and to reallocate the frequencies for mobile data.</P>
                  <P>In 10.2016 Ofcom published a further statement which set out our decision to accelerate the 700 MHz clearance programme by 18 months in order to release radio spectrum for mobile services in 5.2020, instead of 9.2021. Access to the band will cease to be available for use by PMSE from 1.5.2020 and we will not authorise use beyond this date. The UK Government has decided to fund a grant scheme to support PMSE equipment owners that have to vacate the 700 MHz band earlier than expected. Ofcom has agreed with Government to design and run a grant scheme to disburse the funds.</P>
                  <P>Ofcom has a requirement for an Operator to administer the funding scheme for eligible PMSE owners and equipment. Our requirement is set out in greater detail in this ITT and accompanying Contract.</P>
                  <P>A Tender event will be held on the 8.3, please see the ITT for further details to register your interest.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DATE_END>2020-12-31</DATE_END>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>The end date may be extended at Ofcom's absolute discretion to 31.3.2021 if it is required.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <OPTIONS/>
               <OPTIONS_DESCR>
                  <P>The end date may be extended at Ofcom's absolute discretion to 31.3.2021 if it is required.</P>
               </OPTIONS_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
